RBC Hires Fishlow Minter for U.S. Loan Capital Markets Group

-- B y   D o u g   A l e x a n d e r
-- 
2011-07-11T18:36:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-11/rbc-hires-fishlow-minter-for-u-s-loan-capital-markets-group.html
RBC Capital Markets, the investment
banking business of  Royal Bank of Canada (RY) , hired Judith Fishlow Minter as co-head of its U.S. loan capital markets group.  Fishlow Minter will lead the New York-based business with
Miguel Roman, the firm said today in an e-mailed statement.
Fishlow Minter has 20 years experience in loan capital markets,
including working as  Citigroup Inc. (C) ’s head of loan syndicate
North America. She most recently was a managing partner at North
Sea Partners.  Royal Bank is Canada’s largest lender by assets.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Doug Alexander in Toronto at 
